y Professorship","body":"Minot became the third Hersey Professor of the Theory and Practice of Physic, a chair the family held across generations of Boston medicine. Contemporaries remembered him as a leading physician and a brilliant intellect.","number":3},{"category":"death","header":"He died at his daughter's Milton home","body":"In his final years Minot left the Back Bay for Milton, dying in 1899 at the home of his daughter, Mrs. Felix Rackemann. He was buried at Forest Hills, in the wooded hills his family had long summered near.","number":4}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM118","landmark_blurb":"Built and practiced at this 1876 Back Bay house"}],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","display_label":"Boston physician whose granddaughter married a Wigglesworth","related_id":"X03099","link_text":"Dr. Edward Wigglesworth"},{"type":"family_connection","display_label":"Great-uncle of Nobel laureate George Richards Minot","related_id":"X00745","link_text":"George Richards Minot"},{"type":"in_law","related_id":"HD2362","display_label":"married his daughter Julia in 1886"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Francis","last_name":"Minot","married_names":[],"display_name":"Dr. Francis Minot","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780715000/152391090_0ee9991d-4a2c-43f9-960f-605a6e0b09f5_bowgkm.jpg"},"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Physician","organization":"Boston","notes":"Practice at 144 Charles Street, later 65 Marlborough Street."},{"role":"Surgeon","organization":"Massachusetts General Hospital","start_year":1859,"notes":"On staff from 1859 until his death."},{"role":"Hersey Professor of the Theory and Practice of Physic","organization":"Harvard University"}],"education":[{"school_name":"Harvard College","dates":"1841","type":"undergraduate","notes":"A.B. 1841."},{"school